An ideal fluid with density $\rho$ flows steadily, and its velocity field distribution is

$$
\boldsymbol{v} = 
\begin{cases}
r \omega \boldsymbol{e}_{\varphi} & 0 \leqslant r \leqslant r_{0} \\
\frac{r_{0}^{2} \omega}{r} \boldsymbol{e}_{\varphi} & r \geqslant r_{0}
\end{cases}
$$

