Both \(\omega\) and \(\Omega\) are constants, and the angle \(\theta = \arccos \frac{\Omega}{\omega}\) between \(\omega\) and \(\Omega\) remains constant. \(\omega\) rotates around the \(x_{3}\) axis at an angular velocity \(\alpha\), with a rotation period of

\[
\frac{2\pi}{\alpha} = \frac{2\pi I}{\left(I_{3} - I\right) \Omega}
\]
